flowRoot.flowPara: Cronos is a project management application that collates and consolidates project reports of a multi-hierarchical project organization into a single project report for senior management. An essential part of Cronos is the roadmap tracking feature that allows project managers to plan long-term features and projects and allocate time and resources for them, in turn helping senior management make staffing and continuity decisions and gives them oversight of goal achievement status.
I designed and developed the application front-end you see above including the best-fit algorithm for fitting the projects containers in the available space.
